               <p>634. 
               
                  <persName id="t17760911-15-defend162" type="defendantName">
                     THOMAS
                      MAYO, otherwise <rs id="t17760911-15-alias-4" type="alias">
                        <join result="nameAlias" targOrder="Y" targets="t17760911-15-defend162 t17760911-15-alias-4"></join>EVANS</rs>
                     <interp inst="t17760911-15-defend162" type="surname" value="MAYO"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17760911-15-defend162" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17760911-15-defend162" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
            , was indicted, for that he <rs id="t17760911-15-off76" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17760911-15-off76" type="offenceCategory" value="violentTheft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17760911-15-off76" type="offenceSubcategory" value="robbery"></interp>
               with a certain offensive weapon and instrument called a pistol, upon 
                     <persName id="t17760911-15-person163">
                        Mary
                         Davis
                     <interp inst="t17760911-15-person163" type="surname" value="Davis"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17760911-15-person163" type="given" value="Mary"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17760911-15-person163" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                     </persName>
                  , spinster, did make an assault with a felonious intent the monies of the said Mary from her person and against her will to steal, take, and carry away
            </rs>, <rs id="t17760911-15-cd77" type="crimeDate">August 5th</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17760911-15-off76 t17760911-15-cd77"></join>.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="177609110013"></xptr>
            
               
                  <persName id="t17760911-15-victim165" type="victimName">
                     MARY
                      DAVIS
                  <interp inst="t17760911-15-victim165" type="surname" value="DAVIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17760911-15-victim165" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17760911-15-victim165" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17760911-15-off76 t17760911-15-victim165"></join>
                  </persName>
               
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I was in a coach with four ladies going from <placeName id="t17760911-15-crimeloc78">Islington</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17760911-15-crimeloc78" type="placeName" value="Islington"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17760911-15-crimeloc78" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17760911-15-off76 t17760911-15-crimeloc78"></join> to <placeName id="t17760911-15-crimeloc79">Newington Green</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17760911-15-crimeloc79" type="placeName" value="Newington Green"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17760911-15-crimeloc79" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17760911-15-off76 t17760911-15-crimeloc79"></join>; the coach was stopped, but I cannot speak as to the person of the man that stopped it, because it was very dark.</p>
               <p>How many stopped it? - The coachman says two, I saw but one; there was a pistol presented, but the man did not say any thing; he had not time to say any thing; he was taken immediately.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17760911-15-person166">
                  THOMAS
                   BRASSINGTON
               <interp inst="t17760911-15-person166" type="surname" value="BRASSINGTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17760911-15-person166" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17760911-15-person166" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I drove the coach: the two prisoners met me, one laid hold of one horse, the other of the other, and ordered me to stop; they were going up to the coach; I jumped off my box and some other persons came up, and Mayo was taken immediately; he had not time to say any thing; he never was out of my sight; I did not see the pistol.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17760911-15-person167">
                  WILLIAM
                   MOTT
               <interp inst="t17760911-15-person167" type="surname" value="MOTT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17760911-15-person167" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17760911-15-person167" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I was about twenty or twenty-five yards behind the coach when it stopt: when I came up the prisoner ran from the door of the coach, and we took him; he dropped a pistol; I am certain he is the man.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I never had a pistol in my hand in my life.</p>
               <p>'The prisoner called one witness, who gave him a good character.'</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17760911-15-verdict80" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17760911-15-verdict80" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>Tried by the First Middlesex Jury before Mr. RECORDER.</p>
